    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "EM",
    "text": "Yes, one is [? Pirit. ?] The other sister's name is Shari Mann. And Rudy was going to school after. In Hungary everybody learned some trade in a certain time. I told him when it is possible that we would be deported to Madagascar. He did learn to be a pastry man. And then he was drafted into the army. His mother and his grandfather was taken to Auschwitz with his two sisters. The two sisters came back from the concentration camp. And after 1945, they met in Germany in DP camp. So they didn't know they are alive. She-- he came to Sweden, And we met in the convalescent home because all the people who had nowhere to go did go there. And he came there. I was there because of my accident. And after we met, we fell in love. And we got married 1950, December 24. We wanted to emigrate from-- from Sweden, even though we loved the country, because we was afraid we will have to go back to Hungary, and neither of us wanted to do that.",
