  {
    "speaker": "interviewer",
    "tag": "INT",
    "text": "So we came to Canada. That was the first country where we could go right away. And we arrived to Canada 1951, April. Naturally, we were already married. And 1952-- 1952, we got a daughter, Susan, our oldest daughter. In May, we actually wanted to come to United States, but after 10 years waiting, finally we had the opportunity 1955, February 2. We stopped in Cleveland because one of my sisters-in-law expected a baby. And they expected me to take care of her. So I had to stay in Cleveland and take care of her for six weeks. After that, Rudy came down to Los Angeles looking for a job. Which is the time in McGill University I was working as a laboratory technician in Montreal. At the same time, Rudy got a job because of my professor in McGill University, as a cleaner in the classrooms. At the same time he started to study again to become an engineer.",
