  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "EM",
    "text": "--the Statue of Liberty and there are museums from the newcomers to United State. As we were going through the whole place, in one room, what was closed, we did go in. And there was a glass case with a Torah. And written there, that Torah was found in Mauthausen after the war. So Rudy was the one who carried it to Mauthausen. And-- and he's a wonderful guy. He is a very reliable, wonderful friend. And unfortunately, he was a too reliable worker. He worked at McDonnell Douglas as an engineer-- aerospace engineer and electronic engineer for 30 years, during which he became sick. And that is the story of his life. He has three children, thank God. You already met them-- Susan, Nancy, and Donald. And I am the wife, who is very proud of him. And I love him. Thank you very much. If you have any question--",
